        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:53PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 253 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Centereach, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Centereach, Medford, Ronkonkoma, Manorville, Stony Brook, Middle
Island, Port Jefferson, Wading River, Coram, Holbrook, Farmingville,
Rocky Point, Mount Sinai, Yaphank, and Brookhaven National
Laboratory.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
